choices.text:
why does this command give error Permission denied (publickey):

ssh -i \“~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
The error "Permission denied (publickey)" indicates that the SSH server on the remote host does not have permission to use your private key for authentication. This can occur if you do not have sufficient permissions or if there is a problem with the configuration of your private key file. To resolve this issue, make sure that your private key has read and write permissions set correctly, and try running the command again using sudo privileges.
